metadata.name: méduse décapitée
metadata.description:
Medusa's still life, a composition of two art styles that i really appreciate: still life and mythologies.

If a still life usually reflects our edible cravings, I wonder whose still life the freshly severed, still bleeding head of Medusa could be.

Do you have an appetite?

Does the natural focus of a still life lead you to the inner stillness that, albeit differently, the victims of medusa are also likely to feel?

-Lyrithea
